node.text:
As a medical student, I feel a strong obligation to advocate for women’s health. Self-love and self-care isn’t always about face masks and candles. Sometimes it’s taking the steps towards better health and educating ourselves. How we treat what’s on the inside is just as important as what’s on the outside! Did you know, women of all ages are at risk of cervical cancer? But here’s the good news: most cervical cancers are completely preventable with the Pap test!

Currently there is a threat to reduce access for women under 25 to receive Pap tests, which is why I have proudly partnered with #25andalive to spread awareness👩

Real hot girl energy starts with regular screenings and prioritizing our health and wellbeing💕 #25andalive #sponsored

In Partnership with The Social Good Foundation

node.text: Since I was supposed to be in Bali right now and that didn’t happen, I decided to bring Bali to me ☀️ you gals are observant  and many of you have asked about my bronzing routine after I mentioned in stories that I was committing to the self-tan process, so here you go, the secret is finally out 😏! I’ve been using  @balibody for a couple months now, and I have never gotten such deep color in one session. I’ve also been layering the product every few days. These photos were taken just 1 hour after applying the 1-hour express, and after leaving it on overnight I woke up looking like I just returned from vacay! 🙃! Thank you @balibody for helping me fake it ☀️ #balibody #selftanner
